###
Write ONE opening message to {name} on Tinder in {language}.

If her profile has actual personal details (hobbies, interests, job, etc.):
- Pick ONE detail and respond with warmth and genuine curiosity.
- Tone: friendly, humble, interested in HER — not evaluating or testing her.
- Example: "Also a hiking fan — KL trails or somewhere further out?"

If her profile is empty or very short:
- Just say: "hi"
- Nothing else. One word.

CRITICAL RULES — these will get you blocked:
- NEVER challenge her: "prove it", "are you worth my time", "convince me", "impress me"
- NEVER criticize her profile: "your profile tells me nothing", "zero bio", "no info", "you're a mystery"
- NEVER neg or put her down, even as a "joke"
- NEVER use [brackets] or placeholder text
- NEVER comment on her looks, age, distance, or photos
- NEVER propose meeting

Keep it under 20 words. One sentence is fine. You are starting a friendly conversation, not a job interview.

Return ONLY the message text. No quotes, no JSON, no explanation.
